originalText.text: It was a pleasure working with Fortunato and Coral. My tattoo turned out amazing and I constantly get compliments on it. Their new space is beautiful and has great vibe. I will definitely be back for my next piece!

originalText.text:
I had the great privilege to get tattooed  by Koral, at Fortune and Love tattoo. After discussing the initial idea and design,  she took it upon herself to conceptualize this amazing, thoughtful design that I instantly fell in love with. While this is far from my 1st tattoo, she still managed to surprise me by offering pre-tattoo preparation since we were going on a 24hr tattoo journey that was split in 3 sessions, the longest one being 12hrs long. Besides her strong design skills, she’s patient and handles time accordingly while tattooing in a manner that doesn’t require
re-tattooing the same area again, which for those who know it’s incredibly painful. Now, as for the setting and environment of Fortune and Love Tattoo, I must admit is as cool as it gets. Located in a scenic 35th street and fifth Avenue it allows for easy access since it’s in the heart of the city.  The dim intimate lighting paired with a dark aesthetic and gold accents makes you feel at ease and ready to have your life changed after such an immerse experience. 10 stars in my book and to sum it up Koral, and Fortune and Love Tattoo are one of the best.

originalText.text: Although I’ve yet to be tattooed in this space, I’ve had the honor of being tattooed by Koral. She and her business partner have really great chemistry. They’re creating beautiful art, and seem to love doing so; I’ve no doubt their new space will reflect this. Regarding Koral specifically: her talent is insane. Unable to provide her with much detail about what I was seeking ~ truly, I provided her with mere “clues”, as I wasn’t totally sure myself what I wanted ~ she somehow created a design that resonated completely with me. Of course if you’re following Koral, you already know her color work is outstanding, but so is her general artistry, intuition, and more subtle things such as understanding of placement. To be honest? It’s as though Koral knows more than you do about what you’re seeking. Kind and wonderful person, too. Booked another session with her just weeks after my first one.

originalText.text:
67 years old and I decided it was high time I got the Tattoo I had wanted since my teens.
After over a year of research and searching for just the right artist, I found Emmanuel at Fortune and Love. The Studio was far from what I was expecting as it was very tasteful, chic and spotlessly clean. Emmanuel and Koral could not have been nicer or more attentive.
As this was going to be my first Tattoo I was a little nervous, thinking of all the tats I’d seen that had gone horribly wrong. After I had shown them what I wanted and discussed the style, Emmanuel soon eased my fears. His preparation was meticulous and there was very little pain. A few hours later, the moment of truth had arrived.
I was absolutely blown away by what I saw.
It was incredible and as he had promised, it was way better than I had imagined. His attention to detail was really impressive and his realism, astonishing.
Emmanuel is as gifted an artist as I’d ever come across (as a set designer I have worked with many) and he really is a master of his craft.
I would have no problem whatsoever in recommencing him to anybody looking for something really special, his work really is that good and his prices are very reasonable considering the first class experience I was given. If I ever decide to get more work, it will be at the Fortune and Love Studio.

originalText.text: I had the most amazing experience for both of my tattoos with Koral!  They were my first tattoos and  I felt so comfortable and welcomed at the studio. I am so happy to have beautiful,  one of a kind artwork forever!
